{
  "doc_id": "38301",
  "text": "One branch of this work represents the lexical cohesion in a vector space by exploring the word cooccurrence patterns, e.g., TF or TF-IDF. Work following this line includes TextTiling [CITATION_1] , which calculates the cosine similarity between two adjacent blocks of words purely based on the word frequency; C99 [CITATION_2] , an algorithm based on divisive clustering with a matrix-ranking scheme; LSeg [CITATION_3] , which uses a lexical chain to identify and weight word repetitions; U00 [CITATION_4] ), a probalistic approach using dynamic programming to find a segmentation with a minimum cost; MinCut [CITATION_5] , which casts segmentation as a graph cut problem, and APS [CITATION_6] , which uses affinity propagation to learn clustering for segmentation.",
